{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban labels from saying \"may contain\" regarding allergens",
        "additional_details": "Food manufacturers can legally use the vague phrase \u201cmay contain peanuts,\u201d leaving consumers uncertain if products contain life-threatening allergens. We think this ambiguity is unfair and dangerous. We think companies use it as a legal shield to avoid responsibility for allergic reactions \u2014 even deaths \u2014 that clear, accurate labelling could help prevent. We think this practice puts lives at risk and must be banned to protect consumers. No one should be left guessing what\u2019s in their food. We deserve transparency.",
        "background": "The government should require food manufacturers to clearly declare whether their products contain peanuts and other common triggers of anaphylactic reactions. This bill should ban the vague phrase \u201cmay contain\u2026\u201d, which we think puts lives at risk.",
